	iii.	CW has all rights of explanations of this license
	iv.	CW can modify, delete or create any item in this license
	v.	CW has the right to process operations of this license without noticing users
B.	For software (include online services or all Crystal productions base on computer)
	a.	Close-source
		i.	User
			1.	Users cannot decompile all of Crystal close-source software (Crystal software) in any method, the exception is the recompilation for studying and researching
			2.	Users should feedback all of problems they meet of Crystal software
			3.	Users must keep Crystal software in the latest versions and keep network connection while using them most of the time
		ii.	Crystal Computer Studio (CCS)
			1.	CCS should keep Crystal software update and support them in supporting rounds
			2.	CCS can control the status of Crystal software any time
			3.	All creations from Crystal software are CW’s
	b.	Open-source
		i.	User
			1.	User must follow the open-source license (like GPL v3)
			2.	No other restrictions
		ii.	CCS
			1.	CCS can change the status any time
			2.	CCS cannot recall the commits already exists in open-source repos
			3.	CCS can use different licenses in any project
	c.	General
		i.	User
			1.	Users must be responsible for the possibility of data losing and other risks
			2.	Users cannot pirate any codes from any repos
		ii.	CCS
			1.	CCS can abolish any Crystal software any time
			2.	CCS need not be responsible for the possibility of user data losing and other risks of users
C.	For all services
		i.	CW can terminate any service any time without noticing users
		ii.	CW can collect users’ data (exclude passwords, etc.) without noticing users
		iii.	CW need not be responsible for all risks of users
D.	For Crystal Press (CP)
	a.	User
		i.	Users must give the full version of the text to CP
		ii.	Users can determine the length for free reading and whether to join the Crystal Free project
		iii.	Users must give the whole text copyright to CP
	b.	CP
		i.	CP must pay at least 30% of the benefits ($) to the writer
		ii.	CP must pay at least 40% of the benefits (Crystal Coins) to the writer
		iii.	All the payment operations are thronging PayPal API and other official methods
		iv.	All the payment are over dollars
E.	For Crystal Store (CSE)
	a.	User
		i.	Users must be logged before buying anything for that they only need to pay once
		ii.	Users can create, delete or modify his online Crystal store any time with verifications
		iii.	Users cannot recall or change their payments
	b.	CSE
		i.	CSE must provide a security payment method
		ii.	CSE cannot hide the money
F.	For partners
	a.	THE DETAILS ARE DUE TO THE REAL SITUATION, NOT ALL THESE ITEMS
	b.	For partners
		i.	Partners can determine how to teamwork
	c.	For CW
